        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 4:36PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 435 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Willet to Lisle to near Newark Valley to
near Little Meadows. Movement was northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Binghamton, Vestal, Johnson City, Endicott, Maine, Nanticoke, Port
Dickinson, Greene, Oxford, and Cincinnatus.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
